why do people think that black women are loud i just hear people here say that black women are loud and talk alot but i live in sa and go to a multi racial university and the people that talk the loudest in class make the most noise and get into trouble with teachers are usually not even black most are coloureds and whites and that black people are dumb lol you should come to the university i go to you will be shocked i tell you nah when you smart you get called a coconut brown in the outside white in the inside crap oh i get it if blacks are bad they niggas and if people of other races are bad they just bad people why you wana do em wrong in the st place you think women of any other race would smile and take it like a good lil foo if you do em wrong oh puuuuuuuuuleeeassseeee i'm an older black woman the media in america has consistently portrayed us as loud this has become the stereotype for us it has become an accepted norm with no one challenging it some of us are very agressive in getting what we feel is right for us speaking up maybe that's being interpreted as loud in some minds when i was young i lived in a neighborhood that ranged from doctors to welfare families and the only loud woman i remember was ma rose she stayed by her window watching all the children and yelling at us to stop that i'm gonna tell your momma she kept us in line when we're together we may get loud but what group of women doesn't in relaying their stories and talking about their men the loudest friend i have ever had was a white woman from buffalo ny she dominated a room when she came in like ethel merman have a good life ladies mary Hearing impairment Hip hop collaborations Episodes of Lost (Season 1) Social rule Married... with Children Kodocha Avenue Q Sin City Harry Potter and the Prisoner of Azkaban Nigger Sinfest Big Brother UK series 6 Nation of Islam True Crime: Streets of LA The Shining (film) The Doctor Dances Theory of conduct Ethel Merman Daz Dillinger Wild at Heart (Buffy e